def: To recognize; to acknowledge. [Archaic]I do agnize a natural and prompt alacrity. Shak.
The crop of hay got in a meadow. [Prov. Eng.]
The space between two triglyphs of the Doric frieze, which,among the ancients, was often adorned with carved work. See Illust.of Entablature.
A solid bounded by eight faces. The regular octahedron iscontained by eight equal equilateral triangles.
A collection of sashes; ornamentation by means of sashes. [R.]Distinguished by their sasheries and insignia. Carlyle.
An East Indian resin, of a pellucid white color, from whichsmall ornaments and toys are sometimes made.
Connected with, or related to, the deluge, or to a cataclysm;as, clysmian changes. Smart.

Any moth of the family Sphingidæ, of which there are numerousgenera and species. They are large, handsome moths, which fly mostlyat twilight and hover about flowers like a humming bird, sucking thehoney by means of a long, slender proboscis. The larvæ are large,hairless caterpillars ornamented with green and other bright colors,and often with a caudal spine. See Sphinx, also Tobacco worm, andTomato worm. Tobacco Hawk Moth (Macrosila Carolina), and its Larva,the Tobacco Worm.
A concave surface, or the space bounded by it; the state ofbeing concave.
